<!-- WHY -->
<div id="why" class="pg">
  <div class="sp">
    <div class="sh teal"><div class="sey">My motivation</div><div class="stl">Why I want this role</div><div class="sds">The plan matters. The preparation matters. But none of it means anything without the right reasons behind it. Here's mine, honest, personal and in my own words.</div></div>
    <div class="sb">
      <div class="wh">
        <div class="whb" style="width:280px;height:280px;top:-90px;right:-50px;"></div>
        <div class="whb" style="width:140px;height:140px;bottom:-35px;left:35px;"></div>
        <div class="whl">The honest answer</div>
        <div class="wht">I want to lead<br><span>because I'm built for it.</span></div>
        <div class="whs">Not because it's the next title on a ladder. Because I genuinely love helping people get better, I think in systems and strategies, and I've spent years watching teams win and lose and developing the skills and strategies to continue to improve and understand what made the difference. This is the right moment, the right team and the right company to do this work.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="wg">
        <div class="wc wc1"><span class="wci">📈</span><div class="wct">I want to be on a leadership track and I'm ready to invest in it seriously</div><div class="wcb">I've thought carefully about where I want my career to go and leadership is the clear answer. Not as an abstract goal but as something I want to build deliberately, starting here, with this team, learning from people I already respect and trust. I want to earn a seat at the table through results and I'm willing to put in the work to get there.</div></div>
        <div class="wc wc2"><span class="wci">🤝</span><div class="wct">I learn best from leaders I already have real relationships with</div><div class="wcb">I know D'Arcy. I know how he leads. I've seen Vicki operate at a high level and I've carried that with me. There's something rare about stepping into a role where you trust the people above you and believe they'll invest in you the way you'll invest in your team. That matters to me more than a title or a comp bump.</div></div>
        <div class="wc wc3"><span class="wci">🌱</span><div class="wct">Helping other people grow is where I do my best work</div><div class="wcb">I've always been the person other reps came to with questions, deal strategy or when they needed to think something through. That was never a burden. It was energizing. I genuinely want to see the people on my team succeed and I know that when they do, the numbers follow.</div></div>
        <div class="wc wc4"><span class="wci">💡</span><div class="wct">I'm naturally creative and this role lets me build things</div><div class="wcb">I think differently about problems. I'm drawn to building systems, testing new approaches and finding creative ways to generate pipeline or develop people. A manager role lets me build plays, design the workflow, partner with marketing on campaigns and create something that outlasts any single quarter.</div></div>
        <div class="wc wc5"><span class="wci">🔥</span><div class="wct">I'm coming back because I believe in what Acquia is building</div><div class="wcb">I left. I learned things somewhere else. And I'm choosing to come back because the product direction is more compelling than when I left, the leadership team is one I want to work with and the structure, the AM/RM model, the AI focus, the momentum coming out of Engage, feels like something I can genuinely help accelerate.</div></div>
        <div class="wc wcd"><span class="wci">🐾</span><div class="wct">And most importantly, I'm doing this for Dooley</div><div class="wcb">Dooley is my one-year-old golden retriever and he's awesome and perfect. He really deserves a backyard where he can run around and be ridiculous and happy. That backyard is a goal. This role is part of getting there. If that's not a reason to bring your best every single day, I don't know what is.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="qb"><div class="qt">"I want to build something here. A team with a culture people are proud to be part of, a pipeline motion that becomes a model for how it's done and a reputation for developing people who go on to do great things. That's the work. I'm ready for it."</div><div class="qa">Lauren Mazzola</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="ft"><span class="fn">Lauren Mazzola</span><span class="fl">Why I Want This Role</span></div>
  </div>
</div>

</div>
<script>
function go(id,el){document.querySelectorAll('.pg').forEach(p=>p.classList.remove('active'));document.querySelectorAll('.nb').forEach(b=>b.classList.remove('active'));document.getElementById(id).classList.add('active');el.classList.add('active');}
function showPP(id,el){document.querySelectorAll('.pp').forEach(p=>p.classList.remove('active'));document.querySelectorAll('.psb').forEach(b=>b.classList.remove('active'));document.getElementById(id).classList.add('active');el.classList.add('active');}
function showMo(id,el){document.querySelectorAll('.mo').forEach(m=>m.classList.remove('active'));document.querySelectorAll('.mb').forEach(b=>b.classList.remove('active'));document.getElementById(id).classList.add('active');el.classList.add('active');}
</script>
</body>
</html>
